1 insu red. If a roofing contractor violates the provisions of this
2 section, the insurer to whom the insured tendered the claim shall
3 not be obligated to consider the estimate prepared by the roofing
4 contractor. Every roofing contractor shall provide a written
5 notification of the requirements of this section with its initial
6 estimate. The adjuster or insurer shall provide a written
7 notification of the requirements of this section in the initial
8 estimate relating to the claim.
9 B. Any person may file a written duly verified complaint with
10 the registrar alleging a violation of this section. The complaint
11 shall be on a form approved by the registrar and shall set forth the
12 alleged act or omission stated in subsection A of this section, and
13 a statement of sufficient facts upon which a reasonable person could
14 conclude that the act or omission specified in subsection A of this
15 section has been committed. All complaints filed with the registrar
16 shall be open to public inspection. Nothing in this section shall
17 be construed to require the complainant to first file a complaint
18 with the registrar before seeking relief or remedies allowed by law.
19 C. 1. The registrar shall forward all complaints alleging
20 violations of this section to the Insurance Department and the
21 Office of the Attorney General for investigation, enforcement, and
22 prosecution of any alleged violation.
23 2. A complaint received by the registrar pursuant to this
24 section shall be referred to the district attorney for appropriate
